The paper deals with the problem of identifying active users and estimating their parameters and data in a random-access system where users are continuously entering and leaving the system. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
